  <content:encoded xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><![CDATA[<p>So my time off ended a month ago, but I haven't blogged significantly in over two months. New kid + new job + new house will do that to you. However, I spent the time this morning upgrading DevHawk to the new 1.8 version of <a href="http://wiki.shahine.com/default.aspx/DasBlog/homepage.html">dasBlog</a> and I'm ready to jump back in. </p><p>Back when I was still on leave, my new boss <a href="http://blogs.msdn.com/jdevados/">John deVadoss</a> this to say about my new job:</p><blockquote><div>Our current thinking is that Harry will focus on two top-level areas</div><ol><li>Being the storyteller (Metropolis, Connected Systems etc) 
</li><li>Changing the way we evangelize Architecture - its not all about n-dimensional frameworks, with m layers of abstraction, about perspectives and viewpoints, with n-layers of capability mappings, and enterprise frameworks up and down the wazooo, blah blah blah. </li></ol></blockquote><p>I loved #2. Architecture is such different things to different people (more on that later) but I thought John's description about what it's <i>not</i> all about was priceless.</p>]]></content:encoded>
